Vinicius Jr: &ldquo;My debut? It was a goal of mines and I did it, I debuted. Now it's time to return to Real Madrid strong, physically, technically, and mentally to continue playing well, gaining the confidence of the Real Madrid fans.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Vinicius Jr: &ldquo;Playing well in Madrid means I'm sure I will return to the Brazilian national team. I dream of a long history with Brazil.&rdquo;

Florentino Perez: &ldquo;We have gone after Lewandowski for several years but they wouldn&rsquo;t sell him to us. It was the same case with Pogba. Ofcourse he&rsquo;s a Frenchman we like and we&rsquo;ll go for him...but they won&rsquo;t sell him.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Florentino Perez: &ldquo;Marcos Llorente could have gone on loan, but he preferred to be transferred. Zidane told him that he needed to play and because of that, he left.&rdquo;

Florentino Perez: &ldquo;Last season? We have to be self-critical but also take into account everything that has been won. We won 4 Champions Leagues. Others tried to win it last season but they couldn&rsquo;t.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Florentino Perez on his future: &ldquo;I&rsquo;m not worn out.&rdquo;

